    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Marketing priorities for print-on-demand stores</h2>
      <p>Print-on-demand stores break when email treats every subscriber the same. The pressure point is trend cycles, personalization, and margin-sensitive promos. A disciplined email marketing program must coordinate consent, lifecycle timing, product context, and margin-aware measurement — not blast more coupons.</p>
      <p>Priority plays: Trend and design drop alerts; Personalization follow-up; Margin-safe discount rules; Creator and niche community content. Document suppressions for recent purchasers, wholesale accounts, and active support cases before scaling sends.</p>
      <p>Sequenzy ranks first for print-on-demand stores because lifecycle editorial beats newsletter volume: welcome by signup source, replenishment matched to consumption, winback with VIP exclusions.</p>
      <p>Klaviyo remains the benchmark when print-on-demand stores need predictive segmentation and native Shopify event depth at scale. Omnisend wins when email + SMS must go live before month end.</p>
      <p>Track Margin per email order, Trend drop sell-through, Personalization completion rate, Discount dependency ratio weekly. Email ROI appears when incremental repeat purchase rises while unsubscribe and complaint rates stay flat.</p>
      <p>Buying cycle reality: Impulse to 2-week consideration; trend-driven; thin margins. Email cadence must respect that rhythm — not the marketing calendar alone.</p>
      <p>Implementation: audit consent sources in week one, launch welcome segmented by source in week two, add cart or post-purchase in week three, measure repeat purchase movement in week four.</p>
      <p>Peak season for print-on-demand stores requires pausing non-essential flows, protecting VIP segments, and aligning merchandising with inbox promises — governance matters more than new app installs.</p>
      <p>Deliverability note: print-on-demand stores with aggressive promos need authentication, frequency caps, and sunset policies — complaint spikes often trace to offer mismatch, not weak templates.</p>
      <p>Pair capture tools (Privy, Justuno) only when list growth is the leak; pair Postscript when SMS recovery justifies cost. Avoid three senders without a collision calendar.</p>
      <p>Read comparisons and use-case playbooks on this site for head-to-head tradeoffs and execution detail specific to trend cycles, personalization, and margin-sensitive promos.</p>
      <h3>Where POD operators leak revenue</h3>
      <p>Site-wide 20% off on 12% margin tees. Personalization abandon and cart recovery double-discounting. Public sale during VIP drop window. Winback before trend inventory clears at full price.</p>
      <p>Reading path for POD: COGS table and VIP drop sequencing in Sequenzy; {segment.emailPriorities.join('; ')}; {segment.metrics[0]} weekly. Trend velocity with margin discipline — {segment.buyingCycle} — across Shopify email marketing apps.</p>
    </div>
